 Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule, has felicitated with Christians as they mark this year’s Easter celebrations. Sule in a message on behalf of the government and people of Nasarawa State congratulated the clergy and all Christian faithful in commemoration of the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ.  In a statement issued yesterday by the Director General, Strategic Communications and Press Affairs to the governor, Yakubu Lamai, Sule said  “the events leading to the resurrection of Christ were a significant milestone in the history of Christianity, the death and rise of Jesus Christ, therefore, symbolized sacrifice and the divinity of God” he said “We need to be passionate and always make meaningful contributions towards positive development and progress of our dear state and the country at large,” he said. 